  "texts": [
    "This configuration balanced memory efficiency and convergence stability, making DRaFT-Q usable on a single T4 GPU.",
    "It also enabled training of models up to LLaMA-2-13B under tight VRAM budgets.",
    "Our ablations confirm that DRaFT-Q's performance arises from the combined power of two techniques: adaptive rank allocation and rewardweighted fine-tuning.",
    "Removing either reduces effectiveness, while combining both enables significant performance gains without increasing compute.",
    "Furthermore, reward weighting and dynamic ranks act as orthogonal improvements: the former drives attention to meaningful tokens, and the latter increases the model's representational efficiency."
